Pan Africa Insurance Rallies Most in 4 1/2 Years on Profit

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-03-16T13:08:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/pan-africa-sanlam-s-kenya-unit-rallies-most-in-four-years-on-profit-jump.html
  Pan Africa Insurance Holdings Ltd. (PAIL) ,
the Kenyan unit of South Africa-based  Sanlam Ltd. (SLM) , rallied the
most in 4 1/2 years after saying full-year profit quadrupled.  The stock gained 19 shillings, or 24 percent, to 98.5
shillings by the 3 p.m. close in Nairobi, the biggest jump since
Aug. 14, 2006 and highest closing price since January 9, 2008.  The company’s net income increased to 589.3 million
shillings ($6.87 million) in the 12 months through December,
from 138.9 million shillings a year earlier, the Nairobi-based
company said in a statement distributed by the city’s stock
exchange yesterday. Sanlam is South Africa’s largest insurer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
